{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_22","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' references_cache/PMID_19204068.md\"","aggregated_output":"---\nreference_id: PMID:19204068\ntitle: The maternal to zygotic transition in animals and plants.\nauthors:\n- Baroux C\n- Autran D\n- Gillmor CS\n- Grimanelli D\n- Grossniklaus U\njournal: Cold Spring Harb Symp Quant Biol\nyear: '2008'\ndoi: 10.1101/sqb.2008.73.053\nkeywords:\n- Animals\n- \"Arabidopsis/embryology, genetics, physiology\"\n- \"Drosophila/embryology, genetics, physiology\"\n- Embryonic Development/genetics\n- Female\n- Fertilization\n- \"Gene Expression Regulation, Developmental\"\n- \"Gene Expression Regulation, Plant\"\n- Male\n- Mice\n- \"Models, Biological\"\n- Pregnancy\n- Seeds/physiology\n- Zygote/physiology\ncontent_type: abstract_only\n---\n\n# The maternal to zygotic transition in animals and plants.\n**Authors:** Baroux C, Autran D, Gillmor CS, Grimanelli D, Grossniklaus U\n**Journal:** Cold Spring Harb Symp Quant Biol (2008)\n**DOI:** [10.1101/sqb.2008.73.053](https://doi.org/10.1101/sqb.2008.73.053)\n\n## Content\n\n1. Cold Spring Harb Symp Quant Biol. 2008;73:89-100. doi:\n10.1101/sqb.2008.73.053.  Epub 2009 Feb 9.\n\nThe maternal to zygotic transition in animals and plants.\n\nBaroux C(1), Autran D, Gillmor CS, Grimanelli D, Grossniklaus U.\n\nAuthor information:\n(1)Institute of Plant Biology & Zürich-Basel Plant Science Center, University of \nZürich, CH-8008 Zürich, Switzerland.\n\nIn the animal kingdom, maternal control of early development is a common \nfeature. The onset of zygotic control over early development, defined as the \nmaternal to zygotic transition (MZT), follows fertilization with a delay of a \nvariable number of cell divisions, depending on the species. The MZT has been \nwell defined in animals, but investigations remain in their infancy in plants. \nRecent evidence suggests, however, that in plants as in animals, the MZT also \noccurs several division cycles after fertilization. The likely convergent \nevolution of the MZT in the animal and plant kingdoms is fascinating and raises \nmajor questions regarding its biological significance, particularly with regard \nto its importance in genome reprogramming and the acquisition of totipotency by \nthe embryo.\n\nDOI: 10.1101/sqb.2008.73.053\nPMID: 19204068 [Indexed for MEDLINE]","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
